  "texts": [
    "DNN profiles We profile the DNNs (accuracy and latency) using the COCO-val2017 image dataset (Lin et al. 2014) and use the standard comparison metric called mean average precision (mAP) to rank the DNNs.",
    "Figure 10 shows the DNN profiles used in the evaluation.",
    "From the throughput profile, we see that for the majority of the DNNs, the curve starts plateauing at around batch size 8.",
    "Furthermore, we use the 99th-percentile (P99) latency profile to keep SLO violations low.",
    "Unlike the average latency profile, the P99 latency profile curve may not follow the non-decreasing trend (as required in our algorithms) due to high tail variations."
  ],
